rosoft]]|quote=We sold in 1.1 million consoles in the fourth quarter, as we drew down channel inventory, compared to 1.0 million consoles during the prior year. }}</ref> Microsoft stated it will shift focus to the amount of active users on [[Xbox Live]] starting in late 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2015/10/22/xbox-hardware-sales-down-xbox-live-user-up-to-39-million.aspx|title=[Update] Microsoft Will Focus Primarily On Xbox Live Usership, Not Console Shipments| date =October 22, 2015|last=Futter|first=Mike |website=[[Game Informer]]|access-date=October 22, 2015}}</ref> Microsoft CEO [[Satya Nadella]] unveiled at a December 3, 2014 shareholder presentation that 10&nbsp;million units were sold.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.microsoft.com/investor/Events/Presentations/2014/ShareholderMeeting2014.aspx?eventid=151407&Search=true&SearchType=0 |title=Microsoft Annual Meeting of Shareholders |accessdate= January 31, 2015|date= December 3, 2014|publisher=[[Microsoft]]|quote=Finally, our gaming business is thriving with the Xbox One hitting 10 million units sold. I am thrilled to welcome Mojang and Minecraft community to Microsoft.}}</ref> Third-party estimates suggest sales reached approximately 41&nbsp;million worldwide by late 2018.<ref>https://comicbook.com/gaming/2019/01/27/xbox-one-ps4-sales/</ref>}}\n|Custom 1.75&nbsp;GHz AMD 8-core APU (2 quad-core Jaguar modules)\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |[[Nintendo Switch]]\n|{{dts|2017-03-03}}\n|[[Nintendo]] {{flagicon|JPN}}\n|ca. 52.48 million (as of  December 31, 2019)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/hard_soft/|title=Dedicated Video Game Sales Units|last=|first=|date=|work=|accessdate=February 8, 2020|website=Nintendo}}</ref>\n|Octa-core (4\u00d7ARM Cortex-A57 & 4\u00d7ARM Cortex-A53) @ 1.020 GHz\n|}\n\n* The Nintendo Switch was released during this period, but has been referred to as a hybrid video game console, combining features of home and handheld systems. This is why the Switch appears in both the list of home video game consoles and the [[list of handheld game consoles]].\n\n== Upcoming consoles ==\n\nThe following are announced home consoles for release in the near future:<ref>https://www.cnet.com/features/xbox-ps5-and-the-climate-crisis-next-gen-video-games-could-be-worse-for-the-planet/</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" id=\"9gencon\"\n|+\n!Name || Release date || Manufacturer || Units sold\n!CPU\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |[[PlayStation 5]]\n|Q4 2020\n|[[Sony]] {{flagicon|JPN}}\n|0\n|AMD Zen 2-based CPU with 8 cores at 3.5GHz (variable frequency)<ref>https://www.techradar.com/news/ps5#section-ps5-specs</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |[[Xbox Series X]]\n|Q4 2020\n|[[Microsoft]] {{flagicon|USA}}\n|0\n|8x Zen 2 Cores at 3.8GHz (3.6GHz with SMT) 7nm<ref>https://www.techradar.com/news/xbox-series-x#section-xbox-series-x-specs</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of best-selling game consoles]]\n* [[List of video game console emulators]]\n* [[List of video game consoles]]\n** [[List of dedicated consoles]]\n** [[List of handheld game consoles]]\n** [[List of microconsoles]]\n** [[List of retro style video game consoles]]\n** [[List of video games]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Notelist}}\n\n{{Home video game consoles}}\n{{video game consoles}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of video game consoles|*]]\n[[Category:Home video game consoles]]\n[[Category:Technology-related lists|Home video game consoles]]\n", "name_user": "Tanner9078", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eUpcoming consoles)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_home_video_game_consoles"}
{"title_page": "Shyqyri Shala", "text_new": "{{short description|Albanian footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Shyqyri Shala\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1965|7|5}}\n| image = \n| image_size = 300px\n| birth_place = [[Kavaj\u00eb]], [[People's Socialist Republic of Albania|Albania]]\n| height = {{Height|m=|precision=0}}\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| years1 = 1986-1993 | clubs1 = [[Besa Kavaj\u00eb|Besa]]             | caps1 = 62+  | goals1 = 6+\n| nationalyears1 = 1993\n| nationalteam1 = [[Albania national football team|Albania]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0 \n}}\n'''Shyqyri Shala''' (born 5 July 1965) is a retired [[Albania]]n footballer who played as a defender for [[Besa Kavaj\u00eb]] in the [[Albanian Superliga]]. He was capped 2 times with the [[Albania national football team]].\n\n==International career==\nHe made his debut for [[Albania national football team|Albania]] in a May 1993 [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Latvia national football team|Latvia]] and earned a total of 2 caps, scoring no goals. His other international game was another World Cup qualification match, 11 days after his first, against the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=19074|title=Player Database}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nShala was a cousin of [[KF Apolonia Fier|Apolonia]] legend [[Kujtim Majaci]].<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/ish-mbrojtesi-i-beses-tregon-sekretin-si-e-tolerova-golin-e-majacit/ Ish-mbrojt\u00ebsi i Bes\u00ebs tregon sekretin: Si e tolerova golin e Majacit] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|25207}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shala, Shyqyri}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Kavaj\u00eb]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Albanian footballers]]\n[[Category:Albania international footballers]]\n[[Category:Besa Kavaj\u00eb players]]\n[[Category:Albanian Superliga players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Shyqyri Shala\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1965|7|5}}\n| image = \n| image_size = 300px\n| birth_place = [[Kavaj\u00eb]], [[People's Socialist Republic of Albania|Albania]]\n| height = {{Height|m=|precision=0}}\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| years1 = 1986-1993 | clubs1 = [[Besa Kavaj\u00eb|Besa]]             | caps1 = 62+  | goals1 = 6+\n| nationalyears1 = 1993\n| nationalteam1 = [[Albania national football team|Albania]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0 \n}}\n'''Shyqyri Shala''' (born 5 July 1965) is a retired [[Albania]]n footballer who played as a defender for [[Besa Kavaj\u00eb]] in the [[Albanian Superliga]]. He was capped 2 times with the [[Albania national football team]].\n\n==International career==\nHe made his debut for [[Albania national football team|Albania]] in a May 1993 [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Latvia national football team|Latvia]] and earned a total of 2 caps, scoring no goals. His other international game was another World Cup qualification match, 11 days after his first, against the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=19074|title=Player Database}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nShala was a cousin of [[KF Apolonia Fier|Apolonia]] legend [[Kujtim Majaci]].<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/ish-mbrojtesi-i-beses-tregon-sekretin-si-e-tolerova-golin-e-majacit/ Ish-mbrojt\u00ebsi i Bes\u00ebs tregon sekretin: Si e tolerova golin e Majacit] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|25207}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shala, Shyqyri}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category: